cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic image segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a model that generates auxiliary labels for each image, which involves training a neural network. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of conditional random fields, which is a common technique in computer vision and could place the paper in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
